==Russian==
[[Category:ru:Cities]]
===Etymology===
The imperative of the verb [[владеть]] ("to possess", "be master of") plus [[восток]] ("the East"); then [[восток]] is made up of [[вос-]] ("up") plus [[течь]] ("to flow", "to stream"), referring to the [[sun]] coming up (in the [[East]]).

===Noun===
'''Владивосток''' (Vladivostók) {{m}}

#[[Vladivostok]]

